# Richieste manuali attraverso api-gateway (Fase 2.5 — Gateway minimo).
#
# Stesso flusso di auth-service/requests.http e workout-service/requests.http,
# ma passando dall'unico punto di ingresso (porta 4000) invece che chiamare i
# servizi direttamente sulle loro porte.
#
# Prerequisiti: infrastruttura + servizi + gateway avviati e migrazioni eseguite
#   docker compose up -d
#   npm run db:migrate --workspace=@gym-tracker/auth-service
#   npm run db:migrate --workspace=@gym-tracker/workout-service

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000
@email = demo@example.com
@password = supersegreta

### Health check del gateway (non proxato)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Register (via gateway -> auth-service)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Login (via gateway -> auth-service) -- cattura il token
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### /me (via gateway -> auth-service)
GET {{baseUrl}}/me
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### /exercises (via gateway -> workout-service)
GET {{baseUrl}}/exercises
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### /workouts (via gateway -> workout-service)
GET {{baseUrl}}/workouts
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### Rotta non mappata -> 404 dal gateway stesso
GET {{baseUrl}}/does-not-exist
